06/08/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- Efforts to revive negotiations for a solution to the Cyprus issue will resume in September, US State Department Special Co-ordinator for Cyprus Thomas Weston said in an interview with the Greek daily <I>Phileleftheros</I>. Weston explained that consultative talks on the plan proposed by UN Secretary General Kofi Annan will take place in Brussels and Italy. He added that the plan is the only basis for settling the nearly 30-year-old dispute concerning the divided island. Weston also said he would visit Athens, Ankara and Nicosia before meeting Cypriot President Tassos Papadopoulos in New York at the end of September.(Kathimerini - 05/08/03)
